text: I desperately wish I was brave enough to do the only thing that would make all the hurt and thoughts go away If only I could do it  To not have to think back on memories all the time  Imagine new ones that are just as painful  To not be reliant on people that don t want me there  and not feel so abandoned when they want to spend time with people they love  that s not me   I tried so hard  I ve tried counselling  medication  meditation  suicide hotlines  and chat room  Working to keep my mind occupied   self care  I thought at some point  something would click  and I could get better  But I can t stop feeling this love lost  I can t help wishing every day that I would be in a fatal accident  so then my family wouldn t know that I desperately wanted to be dead  but I could finally stop

text: Little strings    When I was younger my Mother would tell me to hold myself together by little strings  I never really understood what she meant back then  I understand now that those strings are the little things in life  A friend to tell you it s all ok  a bright sunny day  the sound of the birds in the trees  I m trying to hold on to these things  I don t want to lose my hope of a better future       Unfortunately my strings seem to be snapping   Day after day it s something new that pushes me down  I m struggling to stand on my own  I m struggling to hold on to myself  I don t recognize who I am anymore  Sadness comes and goes but at the end of the day  I m just left empty  So I stare at the ceiling  hoping I can find something inside myself worth saving  I can t help but think sometimes  I m not worth saving
summary: When I was younger, my mother told me to hold myself together by little strings. Now I understand what she meant. Today I am struggling to stand on my own and I don't recognize who I am anymore. I stare at the ceiling hoping to find something inside myself worth saving.
